  "name": "Widowmaker",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>No vow, no bond, no sacred thread,<br />Shall keep me from the justice bled,<br />Beneath her gaze, with stinging grace,<br />I end his breath, cleave his face.<br /></em></p><p>Legends say this axe &amp; poem are both the creation of an infamous priest of Calistria. The weapon was made for disposing of jealous husbands.</p><img src=\"Art%20-%20Items/weapons/greataxe_black_steel_evil.webp\" />",
      "instructions": "",
      "unidentified": "<p>This two-handed battle axe is heavy enough that you can't wield it with one hand. The head may have one blade or two, and may be \"bearded\" (meaning hooked or trailing at the bottom) to increase cleaving power and help pull down enemy shields. The haft is usually 3 to 4 feet long.</p>"
    },
